	MGM is the best	First the hotel is huge! Something like 6,000 rooms. The good part is that you have tons of things to do at the hotel without ever leaving. But, if you do leave, you are right in the middle of everything. I highly recommend the Ticketbooth a block down the street. I got tickets to Cher for $60! As for the hotel, the rooms are nice and the beds are very comfy. I have stayed in a regular room and this time tried the West Wing. Don't bother spending the $ for the upgrade. The rooms are small and the bathroom is in the room - no door, just a shower next to the sink and toliet. Strange. The regular rooms are much better, larger and have a view(in the West Wing the bed is up against the window). This is my third time at the MGM and would stay here again and again. I used trip advisor and got a great deal with a $25 a day activity credit along with $70 a night rate. By far the best rate on the internet. Thanks trip advisor!	
