bably drinking or gambling.a special line for buffet, checkin and taxi can be huge while in vegas. there were several times of the day where these lines were 30 min long, not with prima...the limo ride, while free, still charges $20 gratuity to your room for gratuity. this is 20 total not per trip. still a great and fun value though.i am actually a harrahs player, and usually enjoy some discounts through their program, but we were interested in a change of pace. i am very glad we chose mgm/prima.if you know that you plan to eat well and see some shows in vegas, you pretty much know that $500 will be spent. so this progam works well. however, if you are on a strict budget, or if you normally get comped anyway, dont sign up for the prima.	
