Nov 2 2009 	Pretty good few niggles...	I stayed in the MGM for 7 days - 23rd October until the 30th October and there was nothing 'wrong' with this hotel as such, however compared to some of the others it does look a bit faded.We (myself and a friend) stayed in the Grand Tower, Floor 8, Room 311 and it took 1 minute to get to from the lifts. I would suggest getting a room with a lower 'XX' number so you are closer to the lifts as the coridoors are quite long! Our room was exceptionally clean, the double beds were EXTREMELY comfy and the towels were lovely and fluffy.Our rooms were cleaned every day to a high standard and there are 38 or so channels to choose from. If you want to buy a movie, you have to leave a credit card behind the desk which they authorise $200 on it (I didn't do this, but a friend did). Room service was FANTASTIC - fast, and the food was brilliant. Most of the staff were polite and friendly and said 'Good Morning' if you passed them.As for the hotel itself - the low lighting is pretty nasty. A lot of the other hotels (Bellagio, Mandalay Bay etc) were a lot more airy and light so we actually spent more time in them, just wandering about. The Buffet was $16 for breakfast and we ate there twice. The service was pretty good, free top ups of orange juice or whatever you wanted and the selection of food was MASSIVE. It does get quite pricey if you eat there all the time, so we actually grabbed a muffin and a tea from Starbucks for a few mornings (Note: English Breakfast Teabags are called 'Awake' teabags in Vegas!)One of the bad points was when checking in, the bloke on reception was desperate to sell one of my friends a 'Prima' card. You pay $500 for this thing and if you spend $500 you get £50 extra on the card + 2 for 1 tickets on certain things... It wasn't a bad idea as such, as we did spend that much in the hotel - however, some of his comments 'You'd be stupid not to do it' and the 'hard sell' approach after a 10 hour flight + being up for more than 24 hours just wasn't very pleasant - I would have said no, but my friend seemed to be co-erced into it.The MGM is pretty much the first hotel from the airport, so we paid about $15 (that included the tip) to get there and it took about 10 minutes if that. Would I stay there again? Yes, as I am more than happy to use the hotel as a base and spend most of my days elsewhere. We saw 'Ka' at the MGM by Cirque Du Solei and it was really, really good. The $14.99 for the internet WAS very pricey and I found free wifi in The Venetian Casino and in the Miracle Mile so only bought the internet for 2 days - it worked fine though.We stayed there as my sister and her Husband got married at the MGM Wedding Chapel - as an aside note, the Wedding people were amazing, very helpful and the service was amazing. They had their photos (which were very good) within 24 hours and they thoroughly loved it.	
