Oct 29 2009 	Good hotel	We stayed at MGM Grand for 6 nights, 10/13 – 10/19, in a Celebrity Spa Suite. This was our fifth trip to Las Vegas, but the first time staying at MGM Grand (although we did stay at the adjoining Signature property once). We found it to be a very nice hotel, which mostly met our expectations, and occasionally exceeded them. We had a room rate of $880.00 for 6 nights, including tax, using the “Exclusive Offer” promo code listed on Fatwallet.com. We thought this was a good rate for a very large room (almost 700 square feet) with separate sitting room, wet bar, and 2-person spa tub. The offer included a few other perks, such as a 2-for-1 buffet daily. What we really liked is that it included free gym access for two daily. Working out at a Las Vegas hotel can get very expensive!We checked in at the airport. Check-in was very quick and easy. The clerk offered a choice of two rooms, 8th floor or 28th floor, warning that the latter was a long walk down the hall. We chose it for the view, also hoping that the location at the end of the hall would be quieter. Room 28-240 had a beautiful view of the southern Strip, airport, and mountains. The room was lovely—very clean and nicely decorated, with good-quality toiletries, excellent bed linens including a European duvet, and one of the most comfortable beds I’ve ever slept in. The TV was dated (not HD nor even a flat-screen), but otherwise everything looked modern and in good condition. Housekeeping service was very timely, unlike other Las Vegas hotels where we’ve returned to the room at 6 PM to find it not made up. There were only a few clothes hangers in the closet when we arrived, but a call to Housekeeping resulted in an armload of hangers being delivered in less than 10 minutes. The safe was large enough that I think it would hold a notebook computer, and there was a small, not very cold refrigerator under the wet bar. No minibar, which was fine with us. Plenty of mirrors, good lighting, lots of shelf space in the TV armoire. The sitting area had a desk with two chairs, a sofa, and a comfy easy chair.The bathroom was large and elegant. Plenty of fresh, fluffy towels were provided daily. The spa tub was so relaxing after a long day walking the Strip! Our only problems were with the shower. First of all, the shower head was about 5’4” from the floor. I had to bend my head to get under it, and my 6’3” husband practically had to crouch. The shower also drained very slowly the first day, which we reported to Maintenance. Apparently the problem wasn’t fixed then, because the next night when I drained the tub, the shower backed up and black sewer waste came up onto the bathroom floor. Maintenance responded very quickly and professionally, immediately fixing the problem and calling for prompt cleanup. But it was a drag having people in and out of the room when we wanted to relax after our soak, and it seems the problem could have been prevented if our call the previous day had been followed up. The worst problem with the shower, however, was COLD WATER. It was usually OK in the afternoon, but in the morning, we had to run the shower for 10-15 minutes before the water got warm enough to bear. Oddly, once it warmed up, it was usually fine for as long as we needed it. We reported the issue to Maintenance three times, but they were never able to fix it. The last time, they just said something about us being on a high floor. Not satisfactory.Other than the cold showers, maintenance and service at the MGM Grand was excellent. The gym was very nice: 10 treadmills, 2 regular ellipticals, 6 Precor ellipticals with ramp, 2 Stairmasters, 2 skating-type machines (great for thighs), 6 bikes, 12 weight stations, lots of free weights, benches, medicine balls, etc. It’s not a large gym for such a huge hotel, but we never had to wait for any equipment. There were 4 big overhead TVs tuned to different news and sports stations, as well as individual TVs mounted on most equipment. They received mostly the big news stations and local LV stations. I was a little disappointed not to get any cable stations like the Travel Channel or Animal Planet. Gym access was $15 M-Th, $25 Fri-Sun (weekend rate included spa access). We charged it to our room as instructed, and sure enough the charges vanished from our final bill as promised with our promo. Checkout was quick and accurate. In summary, we were satisfied with the price and more than satisfied with the room and service. The only issue was the cold morning showers. I would probably still stay at the MGM Grand for the right price, but maybe choose a different room type or location in the hope of getting hot shower water.	
