Oct 29 2009 	MGM Grand - Jail	I recently traveled to Las Vegas with a group of 5 couples - 10 total. We arrived on Saturday and checkin was fairly smooth. Our group was either on the 13th or 9th floor of the West Wing. The West Wing seems to me like you're being given a second class ticket - the room was smallish and decorated in modern style but the style was not functional. When you enter the room you are automatically in the bathroom with a frosted glass sink with horrible lighting and a seperate stall for the toilet and shower with frosted glass doors on both. Not enough storage space and the tv in the mirror while a nice feature didn't work.The rest of the room consisted of a king size bed with a desk and chair and a 20 inch tv and closet. The bed was the best part of the room. The rest was forgettable. The view we had was the top of the building next to us looking north but the window was behind the bed so obviously these rooms were not meant to show off the views.As you walk toward the west wing - the lighting turns from what i would consider normal to almost dungeon and the carpet colors and wall colors change to a county jail gray. Elevators for West wing were scuffed and tired. It looked like the West wing is a place for people get put when they expect you to beat the crap out of the room and facilities and have it not be as evident. The one nice thing about the West wing is its proximity to the exit and the strip. The &quot;back door&quot; gets you out into an alley with access to the strip. We ate at the MGM Studio Cafe and the food was great, prices were strip prices and the service was average at best.We gambled in the sports book which is far too small. We watched the games either in Rainforest cafe bar or Centrafuge - which are both located close to the bar and were much more comfortable. The MGM hotel, casino, shops and pool are all huge and not intuitive and can easily cause screwups - you need to be ready to do some walking and probably back tracking until you get familiar with the layout. Cell phones with a large group are a life saver in Vegas.Cigar/Cigarette smoke in Vegas is nasty and MGM is not immune - it's enough to make me not want to sit down at a table or bar but that's Vegas. Taxi stand was good and service was above par. Dealer and agents in the casino were better than average. Pool scene was pretty good although i did not go to the wet republic or any clubs in MGM (not really my scene).Overall - if I were to go back which i'm not likely - too many hotels to try - I would definitely NOT stay in the west wing but knowing the location better now would be an advantage.	
