Oct 26 2009 	Excellent value stay in Vegas	A great hotel, fantastic room and an amazin' pool area, the MGM Grand is an incredible option for staying in Vegas. We booked via an offer thru' Travel Zoo - just over $200 for 5 nights in the Tower, late Sept/early Oct. Seemed too good to be true but it lived-up to our expectations, with 2 for 1 buffet access (real good value/choice) and free entry to the Wet Republic exclusive pool area included. Yes, it is a very large hotel, and it is easy to get lost (we did every time we exited the lift!) but it's no hardship. And yes, it is a long way to walk to mid-Strip but, given the road-works currently taking place on the Strip, it's far quicker to walk and it's a much healthier option too. The room was very spacious, with a great view of New York, New York from our room on the 21st floor. The bathroom too was airy and cleaned each day impeccably. One day we forgot to remove the &quot;Do not disturb&quot; sign from our door; when we came back and realised that we'd missed the cleaner, we rang them and someone was sent without delay. Similarly, when we reported a problem with our TV, this was also attended to promptly and courteously. For us, the pool area was awesome as we spent much of the day here, though one criticism would be that at 5pm promptly, they begin to close-down/eject everyone. We didn't find pool-side drinks to be too expensive, as someone else had commented; $15 for an ice bucket containing 5xBud Lime was well worth it, as were the cocktails at $9 for a refill of the Stratosphere-shaped bottles (equivalent of 3 cocktail measures). Queues for the evening buffet were long and slow-moving, however, they were certainly worth the wait given the sheer range and choice on offer, particularly the desserts!! Seeing &quot;KA&quot; on our last night (also discounted) was sheer joy and a great way to end a memorable stay here. All in all, I'll definitely be re-visiting the MGM Grand next time, and would certainly recommend to anyone else visiting this amazing city.	
