Oct 22 2009 	No complaints about MGM	My husband, sister in law and her husband stayed at the MGM for 5 nights over the Canadian Thanksgiving weekend and couldn't have asked for anything more!We booked a King Bungalow suite and it was more than spacious enough for 2 people. Sure it was a little dated but really, how much time do you spend in your room? The beds are the most comfortable hotel beds I have ever slept in. Our room was cleaned everyday by the time we got back to change for dinner.Check in for us was very quick, we arrived at 9 pm so there was next to no line. We were also PRIMA card holders, so didn't have to wait in line at all.PRIMA, in my opinion, is a definite plus. Basically you put down $500 on your room, and you get a bunch of &quot;perks&quot; that can really come in handy. You get the faster check-in, you can by-pass the line for taxi's, discounts at the shops, a free limo to and from another MGM property, discounts at the spa, on the guest list for the in-house clubs and the list goes on! We knew we would spend at least $500 within the MGM properties so we went for it and again, it was worth it for us. It also gives you free entry into Wet Republic, which is normally $21 per person. You can use your PRIMA card to charge at all MGM properties so its not limited to just the MGM.We booked tickets for KA with the hotel. By being a guest of the hotel, you receive a 40% discount on the ticket price, which is a nice bonus. We went to the early show and I can not say enough good things about it.We checked out Wet Republic one day...stayed and had a few drinks and then continued on. The drinks are very expensive ($10 each), but its Vegas, you suck it up and pay the price! Had we not had the free entry with our PRIMA cards chances are we wouldn't have gone in. We also enjoyed the other pools within the complex and they are mighty fine! There were lots of chairs to choose from at different times of the day.We did the CSI experience, and it really wasn't what I was expecting. Its $30 each to play and to be honest is just way to easy.We ate at the buffet for breakfast every day and never had any complaints. Again, with the PRIMA card, you go to the front of the line as you are an &quot;invited hotel guest&quot;. People in the other lines tend to stare you down when they have been waiting for a while to get their table and we were escorted to our table with hardly a wait. You can charge pretty much everything to your room, which makes up for the $500 pretty quickly.Register for a players card when you first get there...you can earn valuable &quot;points&quot; for your play. A few hours before you are checking out be sure to go and visit the casino host in the casino, as you will likely qualify for some food and beverage credits that they will take off your bill!We used our limo to take us to Bellagio and ate at Sensi one evening...it was great. There are 4 different cuisines to choose from, so there was something for everybody. The atmosphere was very nice as well. It was $350 for 4 of us, including drinks and tip, which we were able to charge to our PRIMA card.The hotel is big, however its not that bad. It will take you a day to get familiar with the layout but then you are off to the races. The walk down the strip wasn't bad either,,,its not like you should be in a rush, you're on vacation! We walked the strip daily. My sister in law has MS, and she was fine as long as we were taking our time.We didn't find the elevators to be to long of a wait whenever we needed them. Our room was not far from the elevators either, which was nice, as the halls are long. Not once were we woke from excessive noise in the halls or neighbouring rooms.We rented a car for a day and visited the Hoover Dam...words can't describe it. It is absolutely huge! We did a tour of it and then toured the strip as well, on our terms, and went to the Premium Outlets to do a little shopping. There were some great deals to be had there and great brand names if thats your thing.No Vegas trip is complete without a trip to Freemont Street. This is &quot;old&quot; Vegas and a whole lot of fun. We did this on our last night and had a blast. There is a laser light show at the top of each hour, street performers and vendors.Overall our experience was great at the MGM, we would definately go back here. We do like to stay at different places each visit which would be the only reason for choosing another hotel. Go, have fun, and remember, you're on vacation, don't sweat the small stuff!	
