Oct 18 2009 	bad place for a vacation	8 male friends met to celebrate a friends 50th. We stayed a the MGM Grand and it is only a great place if you gamble or want to spend lavish amounts of money. they charge for all amenities including wifi, health club, etc that other resorts include. And everything you buy is 20-40% higher than comparable resorts areas I've stayed at. ($4. for a $2 starbuck's coffee). The hotels here are huge and so everything is a hike and inconvenient for a group to meet or run back to room for something. the casino pipes in obnoxious music at all hours of the day so if you're not in your room there is no refuge to read or enjoy a quiet conversation. The streets are filled with card flickers offering sex, drinking or who knows what. It isn't a comfortable environment if you want to feel relaxed and safe. The crowds are massive, the stores are tawdry, the prices are inflated and generally I don't see the attraction of Las Vegas. We all agreed we would never come back. If you like neon lights, smoking, drinking to excess, gambling, access to hookers, spending more money than you have too, this is the place for you.	
