Oct 16 2009	Great hotel but don't waste your money on the buffet	First of all, let me say that the hotel itself is great. The room was just adequate (standard room, 2 queens, non-smoking), but the casino, shops, restaurants, and everything else is great. The place is massive, so be prepared for quite a trek from your room to the strip. We found the casino to be one of the best on the strip. The decor of the lobby, casino, etc was modern and up to date while still retaining a classic vegas feel. The free valet parking was great, as the valets were courteous and fast. The check in and check out went smoothly and very quickly. The location is great as well. The one thing I was very dissappointed in was the Grand Buffet. We booked an all inclusive package through the MGM website that included all three buffet meals each day in the price of the room, so fortunately it was essentially &quot;free&quot; to us. If I had paid $28 for that dinner buffet I would have been ticked. The food is average and the the selection is not very good and never changes. Don't waste your money there. Overall, however, I loved the hotel and I am likely to stay there again.	
