th and enjoyed my massage (I can't remember my massage therapist's name), and I would probably return, but not go back to Studio Cafe. What is the procedure when a guest asks to speak to a manager, or if meals have long ticket times? Are associates taught to apologize and get a manager?  Another observation about the spa - why is the TV on if the guest is supposed to be relaxing? I realize that Top Chef is in Vegas, but the volume was loud enough to hear throughout the spa except for the sauna/steam rooms. Other than the TV, I was very pleased with the facilities and appreciated the spa attendant who gave me an orientation - again, her name escapes me. Overall, my experience was good. I wish it was easier to locate the email address on the website rather via Facebook or calling the 800 #. Thank you.	
