Oct 9 2009 	Vegas workhorse	For a first-timer in Vegas I would recommend this place. It's got something for everyone: the gambling I can't really rate since I didn't do any, but as for amenities, you get a lot for the price. And on the subject of price, do yourself a favor and sign up for email notifications on the MGM Grand website. They have some pretty decent deals - the least expensive rate I've seen is $55. The rooms weren't super amazing - for that I like Mandalay Bay - but they had the basic things in them. I would downvote the bathroom in particular. If you need a nice tub and shower setup, this is not the place for it. The entire complex is huge so be prepared for some walking to get to the pool or the &quot;food court&quot; or the spa or the tram. Food court - they have a neat little area where you can get a quickie lunch or snack for cheap[er]. The show KA was there when I went - that gets a big ol 5 STARS cause it was AMAZING. Another great thing is the pool complex and I would even go so far as to say it is better than Mandalay Bay's especially the lazy river and the &quot;adults only&quot; pool. The spa was &quot;eh&quot;. The buffet was pretty awesome. Bottom line: it's not anything special but in Vegas that's still pretty cool and there were some great things about it: pool, food court, price.	
Oct 8 2009 	MGM Grand met all our expectations	We stayed for five nights in the Grand Tower and we were 100% satisfied with every aspect of our stay - except the $14.95/day Internet access fee. The room was near perfect - clean, modern, well appointed - nice large bathroom with good tub and shower. The king bed was quite comfortable and an individual thermostat kept the temperature in the room exactly as we wanted it.Great location on the South Strip, right across from New York, New York. It was great having a monorail station right next to MGM Grand for easy monorail access. If you want to save a few bucks, take the shuttle from the airport to the hotel, but when going back to the airport, take a cab. It's close enough to the airport that taxi fare is less than the shuttle for two or more passengers for the return trip.The staff we had contact with were friendly, knowledgeable and helpful. Other than the high cost of Internet access, we had absolutely no complaints and we would love to stay at MGM Grand again when we return to Las Vegas.	
