Oct 8 2009 	Great Time at MGM!!!	Finally decided to take a trip to Las Vegas with the kids, and settled on the MGM Grand, primarily for the lazy river feature at the pool, along with the on-site attractions. First of all, the lazy river was a big hit, and despite rather costly innertube rental prices, we had a great time hanging out in the river and by the water fall. With kids aged 8, 10, and 14, it's sometimes tough to find something that all of them want to do, and the pool area at the MGM is really something.As far as dining is concerned, we ate once at the buffet, once at Rain Forest Cafe, and few times at the on-site fast food counters (McDonalds, Starbucks, etc.) With the exception of some stomach indigestion after eating at Rain Forest Cafe, everything was up to par. Even without the stomach pain, I would avoid Rain Forest Cafe in the future given the quality of food vs. rather high cost. The decorations are interesting for the first 20-30 minutes, but that's about it.Our room was at the 2nd highest floor, and we had a good view of the strip below. There was a decent amount of space, and although we originally asked for a roll a way bed, we decided against it since it was rather ridiculously priced at $35/night! An air mattress we brought along took care of that. Aside from the roll a way bed, we stayed during an incredible promotion where we were provided with food credits, drink credits, spa credits, gaming credits, etc. Our room would have been a great value even if we hadn't received all of these perks. We are already planning a return visit.	
