Oct 8 2009 	Would definatly stay again amazing time at MGM Las Vegas!	Me and the boyfriend stayed at the MGM grand for my 21st birthday, first time in Vegas. A week at the end of September and had an absolutely amazing time. Staff were very friendly and it was very clean and polished. We had a grand tower room which was actually very nice; grand marble bathroom with shower and bath tub, two huge, very comfortable queen beds. Only bad thing was we were stuck with a ground floor room with virtually no view but as we didn't spend much time in the room didn't seem to matter and it was good everything being very accessible and not having to use lifts. One thing, when checking in they asked whether we’d like a free upgrade to a west wing room. I’d read reviews and even heard a couple other people at the hotel talking about this and don’t do it, the rooms are much smaller, you’re best off sticking with the grand tower.MGM has so many places to eat you’re virtually spoilt for choice, the grand buffet was great, $14.80 a head not bad either! And with other hotels so close you don’t even need to eat at your own hotel. One of our favourite things at MGM was the lazy river pool. When we were there is was never too busy, nice and hot! The cocktails were great, shame the rubber rings were a bit pricey to rent. A few things you must do when in Vegas are: Go up the Eiffel tower to see the strip at night, Bellagio fountains, Mirage volcano, the Venetian, see a show. When booking with lastminute.com we got free tickets to Cirque du soleil “O” at the Bellagio, Stunning show. We were front row, we’d have quite happily paid for the seats and would go again. Another thing is take a helicopter trip over Hoover dam, the Grand Canyon and the Las Vegas strip at sunset, a little pricey, about £200 but totally worth it. Book through the Travelocity stands in the malls, much cheaper than some of the people advertising it or booking it through your hotel. The hotel is at the south end of the strip. We did a lot of walking down the strip, it is the best way to see it! But it gets very hot around lunchtime and the afternoon, around 37 to 40 degrees when we were there so $7 for the deuce bus, 24hour ticket is well worth the money, it goes all the way to downtown Fremont street which is quite dated but defiantly worh a visit.So we had a very grand time and would jump at the chance of staying at the MGM again!	
