Oct 7 2009 	West Wing stay with Prima	Stayed in a West Wing room on the 8th floor Oct 2-6. The room was small, as we expected, but it also was a little worn. There's no view in these rooms, housekeeping was inconsistent, and there were enough little things to make it annoying. I'm a Vegas veteran so I know what other options there are in town, and I would probably avoid the MGM in the future...except for one thing:The Prima program. It sounded like a good idea but turned into a GREAT experience for us. We took advantage of almost all the benefits, and easily spent the $500 that was required to do so. One show for two and a nice dinner and you're there. The 2-for-one drinks and entrees is a great deal, and the ability to move to the front of the line for the buffet and (especially) the taxi stand is just terrific. The MGM is (I believe) still the biggest hotel in the world, and getting to walk in front of the masses to get a cab was wonderful. I don't think the masses appreciated it as much as we did though!Other good stuff: Ka is simply amazing. If you want a jaw-dropping spectacular, see it. Craftsteak was a great dining experience. Wet Republic (also free admittance w/ Prima) was a good time, even for this 40-something. The 'scenery' alone makes it worthwhile! Not so good: The West Wing rooms aren't all that hot. Boutique-y, yes...but just getting old. The Sports Book needs a new, larger, home. Actually, the whole front of the place is a little disjointed. The main entry off the stip leads to a collection of the Centrifuge bar, with the Poker 'room' tucked behind it, then the Sports book wedged into what's effectively a large hallway, then there be lions. Oh, and Studio 54 is in that part of the building too. No real complaining, but it made for some serious navigating...Would I stay there again? If they continue with the Prima program, and the other hotels don't figure it out and create something like it on their own...yep. I'll probably opt for a suite or try the Signature or Skylofts...but Prima made it worthwhile and a lot of fun for us.	
