Oct 4 2009 	Has to be done first time in Las Vegas	This is the place to go if you haven't been to Las Vegas before and want a mid-range experience which is good value for money. Whenever you come to Las Vegas you are always going to meet people who got the same room for half the price but this is a reasonable place.It is in a great position right in the centre of the strip and has the biggest casino in Las Vegas. You will get lost in this place. Food is aimed mid-market so there are many many places to eat which is affordable. My first shot in a buffet was over here, I had to do it but got carried away - never to be done again but my own fault for trying to get too much value for money!The pool area is great, please come in the spring and summer when you can really appreciate the outdoors.This place has the size that diffuses smoke so it isn't as smoky as it's neighbours.Inside there is a lion habitat which is a nice distraction, certainly worth a visit. There are clubs and bars, Studio 54 is the famous one which is okay, but dont miss the Centrifuge bar where all of a sudden the bartenders jump on the bar and start dancing, a pretty cool gimmick.Overall this place is great value for money, complete mix of people here and has the facilities to give you a great Las Vegas experience without having to leave the hotel. Also it connects directly with New York New York which is useful. Enjoy!	
