Oct 3 2009 	Nice hotel and pool but rooms outdated.	Upon getting to check in we were told that our room was not available but it would be ready if we came back at 3PM. We had no problem with this as it is usually tough to get a suite before the check in time. When we returned at 3 we were told it would be another hour to get our room but they could give us a room on the 2nd floor with no view right away. Once again we decided to wait. We were told our room was ready and given our keys and when we went to the room housekeeping was still inside. We went back to the front desk to tell them and were told that housekeeping had been done with the room for over an hour. They wouldn't believe us that she was still in there so we just sat in the hallway for 15 more minutes and waited for her to finish. The room itself was a let down as the furniture is very outdated and in desperate need of renos. The casino and pools are great and you have no problem finding a chair by one of the many pools. We got a great rate for the suite but I would probably not stay there again even if it was the best price on the strip. There are many other hotels on the strip that have nicer rooms and way better customer service. I would recommend avoiding this hotel unless you are attending an event or concert in the hotel and don't want to have to take taxis.	
Oct 2 2009 	Loved this trip!	I loved this hotel. We did not have to wait in a long queue to check in however the concierge queue was quite busy when we had to use it. It was worth the wait however as they were very helpfull and printed off maps for us. The voltage on my hair straighteners was to much for the plug adapter and they even called round other hotels to see if i could buy new straighteners anywhere, he he!The hotel shop is quite pricey as is the drinks at the pool bar, $10 for a bottle of water at the pool. I imagine that this would have been the same at most of the hotels. The pools are amazing and there are plenty to choose from however it is about a 10 minute walk from the lobby to the pools and you have to walk past the restaurants and shops in your beach wear. The pool gets very busy at the weekends and plays very loud dance music, it didnt bother us to much but it may if you are looking to just relax.We went to see KA on our trip which is inside the MGM, this was AMAZING, you get free magazines handed out on the strip and we got a voucher that got us a discount on the tickets. We ended up in the front row and it cost $210. The show is superb and i would recommend it to everyone.We then bought tickets to O at the Bellagio for $340....not worth the money. Both my partner and i fell asleep during the show, we were extremely disappointed.There is a bus called the Duece that will take you from one end of the strip to the other including Freemont Street, Little White Chapel and the Outlet Centre. It is well worth the money and far better that the Monorail. You can buy a three day ticket which gives you unlimited use, 24 hours a day, i think it was $17? Bargain! You may not think you will use it as you want to walk but you will as there is so much walking that your feet will be killing you! ha haVegas is amazing and from looking in all the other hotels i would definately book into the MGM again. It was a great hotel with lovely rooms and so many facilities. I loved it and am already planning to go back.Let me know if you have any questions and i will be happy to try help.	
Oct 2 2009 	Had a great time!	This hotel is nice. We had a great time overall. The hotel was clean. Our room was a kind bungalow suite. It was very large...nothing fancy though. King bed with a seperate seating area. We were on the 15th floor in room 306. The bed was super comfy! We had a nice view. Only problem was that there was a drain problem. It made a weird noise for about 10 minutes after using the sinks. We just dealt with it though instead of calling for assistance. Didn't feel like the hassle. If I stayed there again, I wouldn't spend the extra $ on the upgrade though. Some of our family members had different rooms that were also very nice for a much better price. The time we spent in the room was minimal. And when we did....we were passed out!The casino was nice. More than enough slots. Would have liked to see more craps and roulette tables though. My husband liked the sportsbook room. The dealers were very friendly and made it fun. The table minimums dropped on the week days. They were higher on the weekends.. The hotel is at the end of the strip. Would have liked to have been closer to some of the other hotels like Bellagio and Caesars. The cab rides ranged from $6-$11 depending on the time of day and traffic.The food at the hotel was great. We ate at Wolfgang Pucks a few times. Everything we had was great but the steak, eggs and potatoes were AMAZING! We had that twice because it was so good. We also ate at the Wok and I also enjoyed it. Portions at both places were huge. We were even able to share 1 meal between the two of us. Emerils was awesome as well! We did the tasting menu and it was great.The pool was great! We spent our time at the lazy river. It's a very nice place to spend a day. Grab a frozen drink at Fat Tuesdays and lay out! :) The food at the restaurant by the pool was good as well.The hotel is HUGE and you'll spend a lot of time walking. Bring comfortable shoes. I spent my time in flip flops and it KILLED my back and feet. You'll need some support. Also, if you are cold natured...bring a sweater. I found the casinos to be quite cold. Would I stay again? Absolutely!	
