Sep 29 2009 	Don't believe the negatives it was grand!!	I stayed in the West Wing with my wife for a week and before we booked she had read (and showed me) negative reviews on TripAdvisor. Don't believe any of them!The West Wing room is certainly not as big as the suite we stayed in the NYNY last year but it was more than enough for 7 nights stay. Anyone complaining about the size of these rooms is clearly spending too much time in their room, bringing too many suit cases or lives on a ranch. I agree its only large enough for 2 people but there is plenty of space for everything you need including luggage and its contents, as well as all the gear you should buy in the outlet mall a few miles away. Yes, there are only glass doors on the shower and toilet but they are heavily frosted and your cannot even see shadows through them!The beds were massive and just about perfect. My only complaint was that I found the pillows too soft - two in once pillow case fixed that!Lets get the other negatives out of the way:1. The hotel is massive and set over a large expanse. Unfortunately the pools (&amp; restaurants) and West Wing are at either side of this expanse so of course its gonna be a walk between the two. Before you head down to the pool just throw on a t-shirt or loose dress over your swimming gear and you'll be fine. Expect up to 10 minutes walking time to get between the two but trust me, it's worth it. There are so many lovely pools you have loads to choose from. I think it was the directors pool does not allow kids, which is good if you want a bit of quiet time. For LOADS more fun head to the Lazy Pool - a few hundred yards of winding heaven, powered by underwater currents means you can float about taking it easy - or swim against the current for a bit of exercise.Literally the only other negative I can include (and I have to for partiality) was that our room keys didn't work when we got to the room. This didn't bother me too much tbh as it has happened in many other hotels around the world and is certainly not limited to the MGM Grand. Reception fixed this immediately and even said if it happens again to call them and they would come up.Some choice positives:My wife managed to lose a key to our room and also the card with our room number on it. One of the staff at reception had this sorted within minutes and was extremely friendly. The buffet is excellent, although to be fair I have never seen any other buffet in Vegas but the choice and quality of food was amazing.Cleaning staff left our room immaculate every day.Perfect location - plenty of other good hotels around and the monorail is right at the back door.So many fantastic restaurants - I would recommend Pearl (Chinese) and SeaBlue (seafood) - awesome.There are so many positives I can't list them all here but wanted to add this article to counter any of the negatives about the room specifically, especially the size and location!! On a side note, for a bit of fin, hit Bills Gambling Saloon - I think this might be the only small scale casino left on the main strip.	
