Sep 29 2009 	Great value and a great time!!	My Husband and I stayed at the MGM Grand in a Grand Tower room on the 12th floor from September 21, 2008, to September 24, 2008, when we were in Vegas for a wedding. We have been to Vegas on four previous occasions. We were there during the week this time and had none of the problems other people complained about such as loud noises, too much drunken activity, dirty rooms, or lack of lounge chairs by the pool. At check-in, I tried to upgrade our room by slipping the check-in person a $20 and she didn’t take it so we just had a normal room with a decent view of the strip (and the roof of the building below). The room was clean and the bed was comfortable. We ended up having an extra person in our room sleeping on the couch and when I called housekeeping at 3 am they showed up within 10 minutes with pillows and blankets. I was really impressed by that especially given the size of this hotel and the fact that it was the middle of the night. The only complaint I would have is that there is not a mirror in the room itself -- only in the bathroom – so when we had several girls in there trying to get ready for the wedding it was difficult for everyone to get ready at the same time. The pool area was fabulous and we took advantage of the drink specials. We also saw “Ka” while we were there and it was phenomenal. Words cannot describe it. We liked it a lot but thought we probably liked “O” better which we saw on our last trip. We ate at Wolfgang Puck and a few of the other restaurants. The food was great and overpriced because it was Vegas, but it was yummy. We also had a bachelorette party at Tabu on Monday night and they were super helpful and nice. I had no problem with MGM’s location on the strip. I don’t usually wear very sensible shoes nor do my girlfriends so we take a lot of cabs when we are there so it wasn’t that big of a deal. We did spend most of one day at the Premium Outlets and there was really good upscale shopping there. They do rip you off on the wifi for $14.99 a day. I was pleasantly surprised by the MGM Grand and would stay there again – especially given the low prices we paid for our rooms.	
