ey had screwed up on. On the other hand, there were things I really liked about the hotel. Fat Tuesdays downstairs was a plus, and I loved sending my boyfriend for our morning Starbucks that was in the food court at the hotel. The casino was fun, nice atmosphere. We bought 24 hr. monorail passes, which left from the hotel so that was convenient. The beds were very comfy, nice duvet covers. We ate at the Italian restaurant Fiamma, which was pretty good-staff not the greatest. Overall, it was a good trip but I didn’t think the hotel staff met up to their customer service expectations.	
