Sep 17 2009 	Definitely Coming Back! very few negatives...	For my first visity to Las Vegas, I was pretty happy! When you think of Las Vegas hotels, the MGM Grand is one that jumps to mind for me and so I decided to book a 4 day/3 night stay with them. We arrived at 9AM, CHECK-IN wait was fairly short (we waited about 9 minutes), the bell-hops took our back because we couldn't get to our room until 11AM but they gave us our key cards and a number to call to find out what room we were in, pretty convenient! The Hotel room was very nice, except you could hear people in the room above/below through the air vent which was by the window. It made me off after I'd been out all night and was trying to get a LITTLE sleep. There was no MINI-FRIDGE, which I found to be very odd, but we made do without one. The lobby was beautiful, the hotel casino area was cool (we didn't gamble really), the POOLS were GREAT (the salt water was much nicer than a traditional chlorine pool!!), there was always lawn-chairs available. DO NOT pay to get into WET REPUBLIC though, its not worth it for a DJ and a nicer chair. Drinks are VERY expensive in the hotel &amp; pool, but there are liquor stores/convenience stores like 1 to 2 blocks away from the hotel complex, so I recommend you go there instead of spending $50 on a bottle of rum and $3.00 for a 20 oz. Coke!If you are there to NIGHTCLUB, Studio 54 &amp; Tabu are right in the hotel, and Club Rok is across the street in the NEW YORK NEW YORK. I recommend Studio 54 and Rok, they are pretty good and close by! Drinks are expensive though! ALSO, there is a LIVE LION EXHIBIT in the Casino! That was really cool because you get close to the lions, and you can even have a session with one of the Lion cubs (for money of course)!Check out took a while, but they still let us leave our bags with the bellhops and go to the pool while we waited for our flight.The Location isn't the closest to the rest of the famous places on the Strip, but they do offer a monorail (kinda pricey, but less than a cab) to take you South on Las Vegas Boulevard, but if you walk you see lots more things anyways!I would stay in the MGM Grand again, I really liked the layout of the hotel and what it had to offer was great considering how much money we spent for our stay! I was very happy!	
