Sep 16 2009 	Loved it	Stayed for 4 nights in a Celebrity Spa Suite 7 Sept to 11 Sept. Room was great, located on the 21st floor at the end of the corridor. Room was very spacious, well equipped and very quiet (probably as we were at the end of the corridor). The bed was massive and very comfortable.We had booked the deal that included the Grand Buffet and had no complaints. There is a very good selection of food, so could try something different each meal. Food includes carvery meats (turkey, beef and ham), Italian, .Mexican and Sushi to mention but a few. We found the food to be hot and tasty . There was also a good selection of fruit included as a healthier option, for those who could resist the wide selection of desserts. We were surprised to find the buffet included soft drinks and tea/coffee. The pools were lovely., We preferred the lazy river pool as it was the quietest. The other pools played music all the time.The hotel is very big and can take a while to get to the pool and to the strip, but we were happy to trade this for the location of the room. If you stay near the lifts it is likely to be noisier, due to the number of guests. We used the MGM airport checkin facility located in the terminal 1, near baggage reclaim and and were allocated our room and given the key at 10.00, which was a real bonus.Used taxi to and from hotel, which was quick and easy.Overall we were delighted with the hotel and would happily stay again	
