Sep 6 2009 	2nd Stay at MGM would still recommend	Got a wonderful package at a bargain price for 2 rooms. Other family members paid $10 per night more with no food included &amp; smaller room. The 1st time hubby &amp; I had a celebrity suite so wondered how the Grand Tower room would be, No complaints We asked for an interconnecting room was told not possible but kids had an inter-connecting with someone else - Think they preferred it that way! We had 2 queen beds &amp; room had adequate storage. Fairly average hotel room that had air conditioning or heating (self controlled). Room was on a lower floor than I would chose (6th) but that was because we asked at check-in to be accommodated as near to family as possible. Clean &amp; very comfortable. My sister-in-law's room in West Wing was more modern &amp; much smaller without a tub (only shower) and King size bed in front of the window, I would have been disappointed with that option &amp; the frosted glass door on the toilet &amp; shower made it a little impersonal particularly as it is located near the main door. You would need to know your room companion well or send them off to the casino, it was also gloomy down that corridor.Check in/check out was fast efficient &amp; friendly. Breakfast was buffet and good choice. Staff in restaurant were pleasant and we certainly received better service at MGM than some of the other hotels we visited in SW USA this summer. The pool scene lazy river was good. There were plenty of sunbeds around the different pools but not much shade as temperature was over 100, Only disappointment is that I wanted a photo with the lion cubs at the lion habitat. I have already been to Vegas on 2 previous occasions with no success in getting a picture with them. Hubby &amp; kids had it done in 2003. Went last Monday morning 2nd attempt this trip since being in Vegas this time &amp; my last day in Vegas) no more photos come this afternoon between 2pm &amp; 4pm. Arrived at 3pm my daughter was already further up the queue with her boyfriend &amp; no photos for them either, Was disappointed but I think it is never going to happen. The cubs are not there on a Tuesday.One thing you need to be aware of in Vegas that the hotels are so huge, MGM for example has over 5000 rooms. It takes ages to walk around the hotel &amp; was a good 4/5 minutes to walk from our hotel room to our relatives in the other wing on the same floor. . MGM is at the south end of the Strip &amp; monorail runs from there up to The Sahara. You can then cross from MGM over a walkway to New York New York then on into the Excalibur. There is then a free monorail connecting Excalibur Luxor (where we stayed on 1st ever Vegas trip) &amp; Mandalay Bay. I can't comment on the nightclubs or gambling just that there is a large choice of slot machines &amp; there seemed to be an area offering free poker lessons. Internet was expensive at $14.99 plus tax, This was for 24 hours but we needed it as daughter &amp; boyfriend were awaiting their GCSE results so was money well spent. They were able to view it privately in our room on hubby's net book so to me it was money well spent. I think it was also possible in the business centre. Our family who went back before us also were able to sort their airport check-in. Planet Hollywood was $13.99 plus tax as a comparison. Would I stay at MGM again? Definitely. It also seems that you get pestered less with people trying to give you cards for 'Hot babes Direct to you' than you do in the centre of the strip.	
Sep 6 2009 	Good value and Fun!	We travelled from Australia and met friends at the hotel. The hotel is the largest on the strip (at present) so there were delays for check-in, lifts, concierge etc - however they were helpful and accommodated our request to have a room near our group. Getting taxi's was quite easy from front of hotel.Rooms were good- clean and larger than expected. Comfy bed. Not much of a view but could see a bit of the strip. Can't remember location of our room, but it was not quite in the west wing -- some of our friends' rooms were in the west wing, just doors down, but ours was much more spacious and comfortable in comparison. Hotel lobby and pool etc are busy but adds to the fun, in a way. Pay to go into Wet Republic - had a ball for a day there. Restaurants were good, plenty to choose from. Especially good value when rooms on sale $79/night!	
Sep 5 2009 	Very Good!	Good - excellent customer service; the glamour suite!; Very clean rooms; Ready on arrival. Comfortable beds. Travelling on the Deuce Bus for $7.00 all day pass.Bad - buffet expensive; waitress service poor; selection not great; hot food was cold. Pool noisy (with music), crowded.Ugly - slot machines very tight. Go elsewhere.Tips:1. Go outside on the strip for an inexpensive breakfast ($3.99) includes bacon or ham or sausage plus eggs and hash browns.2. Loose slots at the New York New York.3. Get the $7.00 day pass for the Deuce Bus - it is worth it to save on walking.4. Get to the downtown Freemont street if you have never been there. Go in the early evening - have dinner at one of the hotels (we like the buffet at the Golden Nugget - great seafood), and watch the light show when it gets dark - free of course.5. See the water fountains in front of Bellagio in the evening (to music) - free of course.6. See the lions at the lion den at MGM Grand. They are there from 11-4. - free.7. If you are not into eating big buffets and want something smaller - try the New York New York - deli sandwiches, pizza, fish and chips - great price - great atmosphere.As for the MGM Grand Glamour Suite - very nice - big, about 1250 sq. ft. Has large jaccuzi tub (we did not use). But....if you have someone staying in a room above you that has this tub - it will keep you awake at night if they use it. We have people use their tub above us at 11 pm, 3 a.m. 5 a.m. The sound is eye-opening at these hours.Another tip, wear running shoes - expect to walk - alot! And stay hydrated with lots of water - especially if you are drinking coffee and or alcohol. The temperature this time of year was 40 celcius.Have fun! We did. Will be back to Vegas again - probably will go back to the Venetian Hotel where we stayed before.	
Sep 5 2009 	Nickel 	The price was right but that was the best part of our three night experience at the MGM Grand. We booked a spa room on the 23rd floor for $93 a night - a cheaper room would do very well indeed as we never used the large jetted tub. Upon arrival we were curtly treated by a check in person after waiting almost half an hour in huge line-ups in the foyer. There was a &quot;cooking smell&quot; in the room which staff &quot;took care off&quot; immediately by masking the small with a spray deodorant. The room was a great size however it's interior is badly &quot;dated&quot;. Curtains sagged as if they were too long for the windows. Lamps shades were twisted and the bathroom wall had exposed holes were a hairdryer (torn from the wall) had been recently moved to another spot on the wall. It took a very long time to get hot water in the shower. The light in the makeup mirror was burnt out. Provided shampoo, conditioner, lotion and soap had an &quot;odd&quot; old smell. We went out and bought our own soap.The King Size bed was overly soft, however, some people might like that.The closet did not have enough hangers for our clothes. The old television is NOT flat screen and the picture is very poor. The bar fridge has seen better days. There was no free internet in the hotel and were told at the business centre it would cost a minimum five dollars to print boarding passes when we left.We were given an incentive ticket for the morning buffet - 9.99 before 8am. Even though we were in the line before 8 am, when we finally reached the cashier, (a person with no people skills, and English as a perhaps third language) refused to accept the ticket as it was 8:05. We complained the management at the front desk and were told &quot;There has to be a cut-off sometime!!!) I remind you we were guests at the hotel! The MGM Buffet is mediocre at best and I suggest if you want buffet the best deal for the money is the high quality Buffet at Bellagio- you can charge this to your room at MGM. Don't buy anything at the Hotel convenience shop-the prices are astronomical. Instead walk a block down the strip and do your shopping at a huge drug store. They have everything. Just comparing the price of a litre bottle of water: MGM-$4.00 Drug Store- $1.39The best thing about the MGM Grand complex is the Grand pool. The river pool is very popular with children and adults and a wonderful place to spend the morning, afternoon or the entire day! We booked MGM specifically for the pool which is also available to people choosing to stay at the high end Signature Grand at MGM - a much nicer and quieter hotel with no casino. So would I return to the MGM Grand? Absolutely not, but would return to the Signature Suites at MGM (were we stayed last year). The price was right for a night at the MGM Grand but be prepared to be up-charged for almost every thing else during your stay.	
