Aug 30 2009 	Fantastic Hotel! Everything you need!	We stayed at the MGM Grand for a week - there was 6 of us with age range from 24 - 72! Before we went i read a few reviews and was a little worried that i had booked a melon.If you are thinking the same - dont worry! Its FANTASTIC! Hotel - Yes its big, yes there is a lot of walking, but you should expect it, so i dont see why people moan about it. All of the public areas are very clean, there is always a team of people where ever you go cleaning something, i did expect it to be a bit untidy with 10,000 odd people staying there, but i was wrong - it was imaculate.There is more resturants than you could visit - covering every budget and taste. A food court for cheaper options with Macdonlds, a chinese, pizza, and a hotdog place, between us we ate at all these and all were very good. We ate most days at the ' grand buffet'... which is a great deal at $30 mon-fri and $40 at weekends.Lots of choice, but it is the same food choice everyday - however, there is so much there you can eat something different everyday! It didnt bother us the choice didnt change - after all you still go to Macdonalds and there menu doesnt change?!The drinks are included in the buffet price - and at the weekend for just $2.50 you can have unlimited refills of champers!Casino - it was busy, as expected, we stuck to the machines, as we are not massive gamblers the $10 min for every bet on the tables was a bit much for us - we were happy on the slots where if you want you can bet 1cent at a time. Rooms - we had 3 rooms and we were very happy that we had all been put on the same floor all with fantastic views. My mum did want a smoking room and asked to change - they said she could no problem - or they could just give her an ash tray. Great for us - prob not so great if you are a non smoker and you go in the room next, but it worked for us and made our trip easier.Decor wasnt poor as some reviews say, and i have also noticed many mention that the tv is not newer - well if thats all there is to moan about I think the hotel cant be doing much wrong! The tv didnt interest us , as there is so much to see and do there is no time to watch tv!Rooms were cleaned to a high standard - however they did get to us late, in most of europe the cleaners are trying to get into your room from 8am - here i didnt see anyone til after 10am - so our room was not done til 3pm most days. That is the ONLY thing that bothered me at this hotel.We found the staff very helpful at the main desk - i had phoned ahead and asked about a mobility scooter for my gran as i was worried to she would not be able to walk all week ( i was wrong she was fine ) and they have them there to hire if you need $120 for the week - think the day hire was $40. We found them very helpful on my birthday when i asked the concierge to recomend a resturant - which she did, Lavo in the Venitian - she phoned and booked it for us , and got us on a table outside over looking the show at Treasure Island - highly recomend that resturant! Not to expensive , wonderful food.Ka - We booked this show in the hotel because it looked great on the ad's they play and as guests of the hotel you get 40% off - the middle price seats were $90 with the discount. I have to be honest I didnt think to much of the show - the 6 of us went - 2 fell asleep - 2 loved it - 2 thought it was very over priced for what it was!Yes its clever - parts are great - lots of it board me. And i think the whole theatre was split because at the end some stood clapping - some ran to the exit - others like me sat wondering if i had just wasted 2hrs of my life.Deals!!!! Best deal was the buffet , tho the que is long they get through it quick we never waited more that 15mins- we ate at the New York buffet once - never again! There are some great drinks bargins to be had massive 32oz beers for $9 - then refils for just $5! 32oz cocktails $15 refils $8! Free drinks when you are gambling ( you dont get that in the uk ) Free lion habitat, $13 for all day pass on the train so you can visit other hotels, free towels for the pool, Bucket of beer in ice by the pool $25 - i thought that was a good deal others didnt - but I guess i am used to London prices.Everything about this hotel was fab - it was clean , friendly, and you wouldnt need to leave if you didnt want to, so much to do i wish i had booked 2 wks!	
