Aug 11 2009 	Good for First Timers but big and crowded	8th time to Vegas for me and a few of my friends. Most of the time we stay across the street at NY NY, but MGM was a bit cheaper so we tried it out. I learned from other reviews and Vegas hotel stays that where the room is located in the hotel is very important. I took a 4th floor room 5 doors from the Elevator. That was really the only positive thing the hotel went out of their way for us. Don't lock yourself or lose your room key, or risk waiting a long time to get a replacement. The pool was way to crowded - although it was a saturday. Nobody was checking room keys at the entrance as typical for Vegas Hotels. We nicknamed the shower in our room &quot;the elephant hose.&quot; It was way too strong and only about 5 feet high, but it got everyone clean. The &quot;extras&quot; were annoying too $35/night for a rollout and $15/24 hrs for wireless - per computer. My Iphone 3G was spotty, so I got the wireless but it only lasted a little while. They did easily take that off my bill after I complained. But other than those things and being super crowded it was ok. The Casino was also just ok. Lots of table games and reasonable minimums. Drink service was slow, even when tipping big. The smell of smoke lingered even when people around you weren't smoking. If you are planning on playing a lot, make sure you get a players card and use it. You need to eat and charge everything to your room to get it comped off. It's a screwy system, but it's the MGM way. You never know where you're at, but we were playing a ton and only got 1 night free. To give the example, I was comped playing $25 hand/12 hrs and got squat. My friend who played $38/hand for 15 hours qualified us for the free room. You can stay at smaller places on or off the strip and get treated much better in terms of comps.	
