lking another mile we are finally there -- and wait only 15 minutes for a table -- under misters that aren't needed because it's only 76 degrees! So we are soaked before we even order. By the time we finish lunch and get back to our room -- it has taken us longer to settle in our room than to drive there! We had tickets to see Tom Jones in the Hollywood Theater (in the hotel) - we were seated -- we were there early and only a few people were in the theater --we watched 4 or 5 cocktail servers pass us by - even after signaling and waving -- no one stopped to take our order -- when my boyfriend got up and asked a server to take our order -- he told my boyfriend to &quot;hold your horses- buddy&quot;! It never got any better and we never used our &quot;comped&quot; buffet -- we left the next morning and could not get out fast enough -- WORST HOTEL AND CUSTOMER SERVICE WE HAVE EVER EXPERIENCED!	
