Aug 9 2009 	Lovely hotel large rooms clean comfortable beds	We stayed here Aug1 - Aug 4 for 3 nights. We arrived at the hotel early, and our room was not yet ready, however the receptionist gave us room keys and a number to call to see when our room was ready. Because we already had the key, we then rang the number a couple of hours later (still earlier than the official check in time) and they told us our room number and that the room was ready. Ten minutes later our bags were delivered to our room. We were in the Grand tower on floor 22. We didn't have a strip view (we did request one but were not fussed) I guess you could say we had a partial strip view as we could see Excalibur, but who cares anyway as we were not interested in looking out the window while in Vegas.The room was huge. Just a standard King room, but had a long seat , table, desk and chair. Again the bathroom was huge also. More importantly the room and bathroom were spotless. I think we had an interconnecting room too, but could not hear any noise coming from the other room.We booked the room and 3 buffet a day deal. What can I say, for the price we paid, it was an excellent deal, not so much the quality of the food. We ate at the buffet 4 times, 3 breakfast, 1 dinner, only because we were in the casino around these times. The best way for me to describe it, is the food would be the same quality as what you would expect in a food court at a shopping centre. I was a bit put off by a 'breakfast' pizza, but I was more than happy with my cereal and danish for breakfast. My husband had some hot food for breakfast, he said it was a bit tasteless, but it filled the spot.Dinner I had a sweet and sour chicken dish with rice. Other dishes included fried chicken, lasagne, steamed vegetables, prime rib. Dessert consisted of mini cheesecakes, chocolate slices, ice cream. I would never pay to eat at this buffet, but if it is complimentary then it doesn't hurt to try it.Pool area was massive, only went to have a look at it. Had complimentary entry to Studio 54 but did not have time to check it out. Could not get our $20 free slot play to work either, was probably a catch somewhere, but could not be bothered trying to find out how to activate it.So, overall, hotel was great, excellent value (would only attempt the buffet again if was included in the price).The location for us was a bit far down, because we liked spending time at Caesars and the Bellagio.	
