Aug 8 2009 	Would stay here again...	We very much enjoyed our stay at MGM and would stay here again. Rooms Based on the reviews, we booked only a very basic room, and then upgraded at the front desk upon check-in. I recommend this, as the upgrade price was less expensive at the time of check-in than it would have been if we'd booked it in advance. The MGM site specifically states &quot;We are unable to guarantee specific room types and locations, however a sincere effort will be made to accommodate your needs.&quot;  We stayed in a beautiful suite on a low floor, and had no issues with noise of any kind. The bathroom was lovely, with double sinks and a separate tub and shower (although the shower seems to be designed for people below 5'3''.) The suite included a small fridge, bar sink, in-room safe. It also had separate temperature controls for the bedroom and living room, as well as TVs in each room. Poker Room The poker room is very nice - they have a separate side for tournaments and for cash games. Its built specifically for poker and is set apart from the casino, the way a poker room should be. The staff are pleasant, and the bar service is decent as well. Food We ate at the buffet for breakfast twice and lunch and dinner once. I would not recommend the MGM's buffet - even for breakfast, there are much better buffet options. The food was okay, the service fine, but selection just mediocre compared to others. I also found it so strange that at dinner, they served us in plastic and styrofoam cups instead of proper glassware. (If you're looking for a good buffet, the PH buffet is worth the 10 minute walk). Having said that, the MGM boasts a lot of restaurant options for dinner, and we loved the Wolfgang Puck Bar &amp; Grill. The food and service were excellent, and its nice for a more casual options to the other fine dining choices. We also ordered room service once - food was of a very high calibre, prompt, and nicely presented.Location &amp; Service The MGM is a great location - relatively central to the rest of the strip, right on the monorail line, close to the airport, and easy to access the deuce if you're tired of walking. Its a big hotel, like many of the newer ones, but its not set so far back from the street, which we liked. We received excellent concierge service both by telephone and also at the concierge desk. We booked a show, went to Freemont street, found out about the bus system, and located the nearest pharmacy. Since our flight left late in the day, we checked our bags at the bell desk. They have a reliable system, and when it was time to leave, they brought out our bags to the taxi stand, and brought us right to the front of the line! It was a nice end to our stay, and another indicator of the type of service we appreciate.	
