Aug 7 2009 	Great time at the MGM Grand	This was my 5th visit to Las Vegas in the past few years and i decided to give MGM Grand a go.I have to say that some of the reviews on here must have been very unfortunate to say the least.The reception while large is very grand and the welcome from our receptionist Francis, was excellent and friendly,nothing was to much trouble.When we checked in our room wasnt quite ready, and we were offered an upgrade if we wanted.We already had a bungalow suite booked and were not really bothered about an upgrade for an extra 50$per night.Off the lady went and sorted it free of charge a Marquee suite.It was a great start to the holiday.The room was massive with great views and 2 bedrooms also, with a lounge and dining area and a bar! It could do with a little bit of a freshen up but for us it was a great suite.The bed was massive and extreamly comfortable and the shower while low down(i had to bend down to wash my hair and i'm 5ft11)was powerful and plenty of hot water, although it took a few minutes to warm up some days.There was plenty of storage and the beds were made and room cleaned twice a day.Maria the housekeeper was excellent.There was even a fridge to keep our beers cold!! The hotel itself is a big hotel but not too big to get lost in.The casino is massive and there are plenty of slots and tables to play on.One of the things that did annoy me slightly was the fact they change the price of the card games.This depended on how busy or popular they were at times during the day.You could play poker for 10$ and come back and hour later and the same table would be 20$ a hand for example.This was a little annoying.Other then that the drinks were plentiful and the service was normally with a smile.We ate a couple of times at the buffett, and i have to say i thought the choice on offer had declined a little from last time i was here.The food was lovely and cooked well but the choice available was less then in previoue years.We also ate in Diegos which was excellent and quite resonably priced also.One place to eat just outside the hotel though is Outback steak house next to M&amp;M'S store.The food there was excellent and one of the best steaks i've ever tasted. The pool area was awesome with about 5 pools to choose from and a lazy river.The water was warm but not too warm as someone else mentioned,just enough to take the edge off the heat during the day.The poolside drink service was excellent as to was the food on offer round the pool area.We were a little worried about how long it would take to walk to the pool area from our room as the hotel was so big,but it took only 10mins and the walk was quite pleasant anyway.All in all we had a great stay here at MGM and i wouldn't hesitate to stay here again. I felt the atmosphere and the staff were first class and for the one of the biggest hotels in the world i think they get it right a lot more often then they get it wrong.	
