Aug 5 2009 	MGM Grand just not what it used to be	This was my third stay at MGM and I noticed a huge decline in customer service. From a 40 minute wait for a roll of toilet paper to blatant attitude when addressing a room overcharge, the MGM just isn't what it used to be. We arrived at noon and were promised a room at 3pm that was ready at 3:30PM, which was fine. The room was clean with a decent sized bathroom and nice view of the strip. The beds were old, too soft for me, and sort of dipped in to the center. The safe was broken but we did not ask for it to be fixed.On many occasions, we requested hotel information from concierge only to find it it was incorrect (such as the food court was open later than they said).We didn't eat anywhere fancy here but the buffet was mediocre. Their big draw in to the dinner buffet is King Crab only to find out it is actually Snow Crab. In addition to that, the legs are cut in half and are served cold. Also, they offer an all day buffet pass for $30. The problem was many of the same dishes are served for both the lunch and dinner meals. If you are a vegetarian, you might as well just bring your own food because after all the main restaurants close, your only option for food here is a slice of cheese pizza - unless you want an $18 omelet with dried up hash browns. On day one, we all went down for a swim only to find the pools to be extremely warm and cloudy -- not my idea of a refreshing swim. The lazy river was cooler in temperature and lots of fun; however, it closes earlier than the pools. They do not allow you to bring in your own flotation device (Mandalay Bay does). The only option is to rent one from them for somewhere around $20 per day. MGM Grand's casino is huge. If you play blackjack, expect to pay $25 per hand. The only other option was scarce $15 dollar per hand tables (if you can find them), which you could expect a 30 minute wait to get a seat. Cocktail service while gambling was very good - as long as you tip them at least a dollar a drink, they keep coming back and this includes while playing video/slot machines.Overall, this wasn't an awful place to stay; we were just disappointed in the decline of customer service compared to prior stays. The MGM Grand is funding the new City Center Project. According to local friends in Las Vegas, MGM Grand had just terminated 400 members of their staff. *just a quick note regarding the tram going from excaliber to mandalay bay - it stops running at 10PM these days.	
