Aug 5 2009 	Not what we expected really disappointed	On first impressions were of terrible, impersonal service - we had reserved and paid for a Grand Tower Double Room months in advance for the second leg of our honeymoon but when we arrived the room wasn't available! We were instead put in a small room with tiny window, one chair and bathroom within the actual bedroom without being informed that it wasn't the one we had reserved. We had to que for another 20 minutes to inform reception that we had been put in the wrong room only to be told we had to wait until midday the following day for our room! Midday came and went, still no sign of our room, an apology or compensation; finally at 3:30pm it was ready leaving us to haul our luggage across the whole complex! On arriving in our room we found half drunk coffee cups, water bottles and used toiletries in the bath - not impressed. After queing for 20 minutes for a fourth time in less than 24hours we were moved to another room and only got an apology after demanding one! The room we were eventually given was quite nice but you don't get a fridge or tea/coffee making facilities. On our experience of that terrible night first night of not being able to unpack and being given an inadequate room and a wasted day waiting for our room meant that we will defiantely NOT be coming back here or recommending to anyone when you can get a nicer room for a better price further down the strip (and no doubt better service)The Grand buffet was good value for money but gets very busy, the que for the clubs were rediculously long and we couldn't get anywhere near the pool, the poolside cabanas cost more than a room to rent!All in all we were unbelievably dissapointed with this hotel and lef feeling quite dissatisfied with it - so much so we have compalined to the Travel Agency we booked through.	
Aug 5 2009 	Loved our room!	This was our first time to Las Vegas and to the MGM Grand. We absolutely loved loved loved our room in the Grand Tower. We were on the 12th floor for 4 nights/5 days. It was huge, clean and updated. I took pictures which I will post.The buffet was awesome. We booked a deal that allowed us free access to the buffet 3x a day EACH. The food was tastey and although sometimes the lines appeared long, they went very fast. The front desk was hugely accomodating.There is one game that only the MGM Grand has that was so entertaining, we played it for hours. It was the old racing ponies game. Who knew we could have that much fun rooting for 5 plastic ponies! :DA negative is that we found the casino to be way too smokey and I actually ended up with a soar throat from the smoke for 2 days while there. Our experience would have been enhanced greatly has smoking not been allowed but that said, we went in all the other hotels and almost every one of those on the strip was actually worse.Another negative was Studio 54. It was horribly smokey (people smoking ON the dance floor), drinks were too high priced (considering they are free just outside the door) and it was too crowded. We gave it a thumbs down but the rest of our experience was &quot;grand&quot;. (sorry, had to do it!)All in all we'd definitely stay at the MGM Grand again....we loved our room that much.LB in GA	
Aug 5 2009 	Great time @ MGM Grand	This was my first trip to Vegas, my boyfriend took me for my birthday. I had a great time and can't wait to go back!Check In: the wait wasnt bad, we arrived at 12 noon and our room wasn't ready til 3. Which was fine because we walked the strip and got to see the water show at the Bellagio. When we came back and went to our room, they gave us a room with 2 queen beds instead of the 1 king that we booked. We called the front desk and they changed our room right away. It was annoying though after doing all that walking to have bring our luggage back down to the lobby to get the key then go back up. And we had to get back on line, which really sucked. It would have been nice if they would have brought the key up to the wrong room we were in or atleast not make us wait on line again.Room: When we got to the right room, it was very clean. Our room was on the 5th floor and had a view of a roof. It would have been nice to have a better view, but I didnt really care much because its not like we sat in the room the whole time. Plus I got to see the Vegas lights at night while we walked the strip. A refrigerator would have been nice too have but once again no big deal. Bed was soft and comfy.Dining: We ate at Wolfgang puck and Fiama's. The food at Wolfgang Puck was excellent! Service was great, no wait because we made reservations. Fiama's was another good restaurant. We also made reservations there, so no wait. I enjoyed the food and the service was great. Entertainment: We saw David Copperfield at MGM and he was amazing! I definately recommend to see it. We went to a bar in the casino, good drinks, music.The hotel was very big, there was alot ot see, I had a wonderful stay!	
Aug 4 2009 	Another great stay	We stayed at the MGM in 2008 and it enjoyed it, so we decided to stay here again on our trip this year. I still found the casino to be busy and full of atmosphere. The pool area is great and there is lots of choice for things to eat. We particularly enjoyed eating at Wolfgang Puck's. There was a short wait at check-in, service was polite. The main difference this time around was the fact that we were offered an 'upgrade' to a West wing room, upon check-in. Remembering negative reviews on here of the rooms, I was a little dubious, but we decided to try it out. The room itself is much smaller, but this wasn't a problem at all. It was strange at first to walk straight into the bathroom area, but it was sleek and clean, and the tv in the mirror was a novelty. The shower area was lovely. There was lots of storage room and the bed was very comfortable. The room was very clean and kept that way for the duration of our stay. Unlike our previous stay, there was absolutely no noise from surrounding rooms, something we really appreciated. The view from our particular room was non-existent, just a wall, but this wasn't really a problem for us. There was a side entrance onto the Strip, not far from the elevators, we found this to be very convinient. The only negative I can describe is that the room was a little too dark, and the lighting wasn't adequate enough. I would certainly recommend the MGM. Yes, it is large and impersonal, but I quite like that when staying in Vegas!	
Aug 4 2009 	Excellent value for money	We've just got back from a weeks stay at the MGM and found it to be just what we needed. We booked online direct with the hotel and got a deal that included daily access for 2 to the buffett. We stayed on the 10th floor in the west wing which is a smaller room but more modern, it was clean and comfy. This was a free upgrade at checkin probably because we are a couple and the bathroom is not very private in these rooms. Its position was close to the elevator and only a minute from the buffett and exit right onto the strip which was great. Also the bus (the duece) stop is right outside which is dead handy. A 3 day pass is $15 and will take you up and down the strip, to freemont st in north and outlet mall and vegas sign in the south. Is a bit slow when the strip is busy but quicker than walking and air con is great when its so hot. People comment that the mgm is big and yes it is but all the hotels on th strip are! Also the bellagio, venetian and caesers are probably nicer but they are also about 3 times the price.Staff were really friendly and the food in the buffett was good. Casino is pretty similar to all the other hotels with the exception of bellagio and cesaers which are a little nicer.Only downside is the small number of shops in the hotel but the miracle mile mall is about a 5-10 minute walk or one stop on the bus.We loved vegas and saw lots. For a nice drink go to the mix bar at The Hotel, Mandaly Bay. Bit expensive but well worth it for the view of the whole strip. Jersey Boys was brilliant and KA which is in mgm was amazing!All in all this is a great hotel if you get a good price and especially if its your first trip to vegas. Cant wait to go back soon!	
Aug 4 2009 	Great stay	Stayed in a comped king room in the main tower ( 16th floor) from July 26 to 29. Service was excellent at all levels; valet parkin, check-in, bell service, housekeeping,etc.. The pool is fantastic and not over crowded. Considering the size of the place, everyone on staff was freindly and efficient. Absolutely no complaints, it was a great stay.	
